abstract: Deere & Company reports drop in quarterly earnings that is not as dire as expected; company says it is well positioned to weather further declines, and expects to remain 'solidly profitable' in 2016.
lead_paragraph: Deere & Company reported a drop in quarterly earnings that was not as steep as Wall Street expected and gave a less dire outlook than analysts had feared.

headline.main: Earnings Drop at Deere, but Beat Analysts’ Expectations
headline.print_headline: Earnings Drop at Deere, but Beat Analysts’ Expectations
